WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:23.600 --> 00:27.186
♪

00:36.313 --> 00:39.231
Fuck you, you fuckin' cunts.

00:39.282 --> 00:41.617
[Door closes]

00:43.286 --> 00:44.870
[Man groaning]

00:46.289 --> 00:47.823
Hey.

00:47.874 --> 00:50.159
MAN: Hey.

00:50.161 --> 00:52.078
Please.

01:17.405 --> 01:19.989
[Distant dog barking]

01:39.393 --> 01:41.094
[Grunting]

01:49.520 --> 01:51.104
[Whimpering]

02:31.145 --> 02:32.612
[Breathlessly] Please.

02:32.646 --> 02:34.981
Please don't.

02:35.032 --> 02:36.983
Pl-please.

02:37.034 --> 02:38.952
Please. Please.

02:38.986 --> 02:41.488
[Crying] Don't. Please stop.

02:41.539 --> 02:43.623
Please. Please.

02:43.657 --> 02:45.625
Please stop.

02:45.659 --> 02:46.910
Don't.

02:46.961 --> 02:48.211
Please...

02:48.245 --> 02:49.429
♪

02:49.463 --> 02:51.331
Stop!

02:51.382 --> 02:54.551
Please...

02:54.585 --> 02:55.869
Stop...

02:57.805 --> 03:00.757
♪

04:28.495 --> 04:30.530
[Sustained clattering]

04:37.688 --> 04:39.822
[Clattering stops]

04:42.860 --> 04:45.912
[Clatters pan]

04:45.946 --> 04:48.031
[Tires squeal]

04:50.200 --> 04:52.535
Where is everyone going?

04:52.537 --> 04:54.671
[Van door closes]

05:00.127 --> 05:02.795
Whatever happened, I want to help.

05:14.858 --> 05:16.976
[Brakes screech]

05:22.235 --> 05:24.004
_

06:01.655 --> 06:03.773
[Dogs barking]

06:07.444 --> 06:09.162
Out of the way, goddamn it! Move aside!

06:10.581 --> 06:15.178
[Dog yelps]

07:04.561 --> 07:06.562
[Gasps]

07:06.597 --> 07:08.514
[Distant dog barking]

07:08.565 --> 07:10.566
MAN ON TV: Thanks, Brad.

07:10.601 --> 07:12.568
I'm here at the Heaven's Converts compound

07:12.603 --> 07:14.403
in Noma, Florida, where cult members

07:14.438 --> 07:16.439
recently opened fire on ATFEC agents.

07:16.490 --> 07:18.991
Tensions between the cult
and the agency have been

07:19.026 --> 07:21.277
escalating for days, starting when ATFEC...

07:21.328 --> 07:22.695
[Turns off TV]

07:36.343 --> 07:37.960
[Sniffs]

07:45.052 --> 07:46.519
Mornin'.

07:46.553 --> 07:47.887
Hey, I'm leaving in 10 minutes.

07:47.938 --> 07:49.288
You want a ride to school?

07:49.323 --> 07:50.690
[Groggily] Mm-mmm.

07:50.724 --> 07:52.942
Have you seen a bunch of my white shirts?

07:52.976 --> 07:54.393
No.

07:54.444 --> 07:57.196
- You sure?
- Yes.

08:00.567 --> 08:02.535
Morning, Mr. Garvey.

08:02.569 --> 08:04.704
You want me to make coffee?

08:09.076 --> 08:10.376
[Beeping]

08:10.410 --> 08:11.827
Hey!

08:11.862 --> 08:14.380
Did you turn the alarm off last night?

08:14.414 --> 08:15.881
JILL: Nope.

08:15.916 --> 08:17.416
It wasn't on.

08:17.467 --> 08:20.403
Yeah, it was. I set it to "Stay."

08:20.428 --> 08:22.828
WOMAN'S VOICE: Motion detector deactivated.

08:22.858 --> 08:24.544
Looks like you mastered it.

08:25.645 --> 08:27.979
[Doorbell rings]

08:41.918 --> 08:43.500
_

08:44.078 --> 08:45.663
[Sighs]

08:47.132 --> 08:48.749
Where is she?

09:07.002 --> 09:08.603
Are you surprised?

09:10.439 --> 09:13.691
We want them to remember
something they want to forget.

09:13.742 --> 09:17.078
They weren't just gonna
leave us alone, right?

09:17.112 --> 09:19.747
It was only a matter of time.

09:26.788 --> 09:30.041
I guess I should be scared, but...

09:30.092 --> 09:32.043
I'm not.

09:32.094 --> 09:34.462
Is that weird?

09:38.750 --> 09:42.386
♪

09:49.227 --> 09:51.862
MEG'S VOICE: Oh, fuck.

09:53.940 --> 09:57.735
[Echoing] I just hope she
didn't have to suffer too much.

09:59.121 --> 10:01.322
[Gasping]

10:01.373 --> 10:03.708
- Are you OK?
- [Hyperventilating]

10:03.742 --> 10:05.710
Hold on.

10:05.744 --> 10:07.712
It's OK.

10:07.746 --> 10:09.380
Laurie, it's OK.

10:09.414 --> 10:11.682
Laurie. Oh, God.

10:11.717 --> 10:13.884
I think we need some help!

10:13.919 --> 10:16.420
Laurie, it's OK, it's OK.

10:16.422 --> 10:17.922
It's OK.

10:17.956 --> 10:19.924
[Whimpering]

10:19.926 --> 10:22.059
She can't breathe.

10:24.529 --> 10:26.480
It's OK, it's OK.

10:26.515 --> 10:28.482
Help!

10:28.517 --> 10:30.568
It's OK.

10:30.602 --> 10:32.203
Somebody, please help!

10:32.203 --> 10:34.621
[Police radio chatter]

10:34.623 --> 10:37.690
KEVIN: Hey! What are you doing? Hey!

10:37.725 --> 10:39.459
- You got the rocks?
- MAN: What?

10:39.510 --> 10:41.427
The rocks.

10:41.462 --> 10:44.464
Look, we need the pictures of
position before you can bag them.

10:44.515 --> 10:46.432
Yeah. OK, sorry.

10:46.467 --> 10:49.369
LOU: Give me a break, all right?
She lived with you for a year.

10:49.403 --> 10:51.938
You got no emergency contact, nobody?

10:53.557 --> 10:54.974
[Lou scoffs] "No family."

10:54.976 --> 10:56.943
Uh-huh. Well, I guess
she just grew on a tree.

10:56.977 --> 10:58.811
You get statements from
everyone in their search party?

10:58.813 --> 11:00.563
Yes, sir. Mike's at the Biggie,

11:00.614 --> 11:03.116
getting yellow pads in bulk.

11:03.150 --> 11:05.485
I need you off the streets.

11:05.487 --> 11:07.987
I don't have the resources to protect you.

11:07.989 --> 11:10.490
I know, yeah. Tell me
to fuck off. I get it.

11:10.726 --> 11:12.825
_

11:13.043 --> 11:14.744
Oh. Good.

11:14.795 --> 11:16.579
Thanks.

11:17.998 --> 11:19.999
DENNIS: Hey, uh, Chief,
one of the witnesses says

11:20.001 --> 11:22.552
he's gonna be late for his
ballroom dancing lesson.

11:22.586 --> 11:24.671
OK if I let him go?

11:33.931 --> 11:36.933
Your boys gonna give me my gun back?

11:36.984 --> 11:39.747
It doesn't shoot rocks.

11:39.749 --> 11:41.115
What were you doing out here?

11:41.117 --> 11:42.616
Drinking beers,

11:42.618 --> 11:44.585
star-gazing.

11:44.619 --> 11:47.788
Hell, you could have been my alibi
if you didn't keep blowing me off.

11:47.790 --> 11:48.956
Hey, Dean.

11:48.958 --> 11:50.424
Burt.

11:51.843 --> 11:53.844
We have an arrangement.

11:53.878 --> 11:55.796
Population control.

11:55.798 --> 11:58.298
[Tape rips] Oh, shit!

11:58.300 --> 11:59.800
Hey, careful, goddamn it!

11:59.851 --> 12:01.301
[Laughs]

12:01.352 --> 12:03.637
Fuckin' horrific.

12:08.977 --> 12:11.111
[Overlapping chatter]

12:13.148 --> 12:15.816
Is that the best you can do?

12:19.788 --> 12:22.489
KEVIN: Sorry to bother you, but
could I speak with my daughter?

12:22.491 --> 12:24.625
Problem.

12:33.835 --> 12:35.302
[Sobs]

12:35.336 --> 12:37.504
Jill. Jill. Honey.

12:37.506 --> 12:39.339
Jill, what's wrong?

12:39.390 --> 12:41.341
Jill? Jill? Wait.

12:41.392 --> 12:42.843
Just tell me.

12:42.845 --> 12:44.645
Tell me what happened to her.

12:44.679 --> 12:46.707
What happened to her?

12:46.707 --> 12:50.162
Oh, no, no. Your mom's OK.

12:50.164 --> 12:52.164
Then why are you here?

12:52.166 --> 12:53.632
[Sobbing]

12:53.667 --> 12:57.086
Last night a woman was
attacked, in the G.R.,

12:57.137 --> 12:59.805
and I wanted you to hear it from
me first so you wouldn't worry.

12:59.840 --> 13:01.841
Please don't tell your friends.

13:01.843 --> 13:03.893
[Sobs]

13:03.927 --> 13:06.345
I want you home before dark.

13:06.396 --> 13:09.732
You and Aimee order a
pizza. I'm gonna work late.

13:09.766 --> 13:12.151
Might not see you till the morning, OK?

13:12.185 --> 13:14.320
I'll text you.

13:15.689 --> 13:17.156
OK, yeah.

13:22.279 --> 13:25.164
I shouldn't have cried. [Exhales]

13:25.198 --> 13:27.700
She wouldn't have cried for me.

13:31.037 --> 13:33.539
GIRL: OK. Ready? OK.

13:33.590 --> 13:36.091
[Girls grunt]

13:36.126 --> 13:38.210
[Man groaning]

13:41.097 --> 13:44.216
I understand we had a rough morning.

13:44.267 --> 13:46.268
[Sighs] Sorry.

13:46.303 --> 13:48.771
Compound fracture.

13:48.805 --> 13:51.273
OK. I had a look at your tests.

13:51.308 --> 13:54.560
Everything seems normal.
Let's have a listen.

13:58.565 --> 14:00.482
All right.

14:00.534 --> 14:04.737
May I ask how many cigarettes
a day you're smoking?

14:06.907 --> 14:10.743
OK, what you experienced was
most likely a panic attack.

14:10.794 --> 14:13.379
If it happens again, take two of these.

14:13.413 --> 14:15.915
If you need more, you're
gonna need a prescription

14:15.966 --> 14:18.417
from a psychiatrist.

14:18.468 --> 14:20.586
OK? You're free to go.

15:01.502 --> 15:03.124
_

15:11.110 --> 15:14.729
♪

15:31.663 --> 15:34.248
"Is the victim a member of an organization

15:34.299 --> 15:36.250
"that claims an
independent religious belief

15:36.301 --> 15:38.636
not listed on the AWR?" Check.

15:38.670 --> 15:41.639
"Is the membership of the
organization currently comprised

15:41.673 --> 15:44.058
- of more than 40 individuals?"
- It was not your call to make!

15:44.092 --> 15:46.010
Check. "Has there been a pattern

15:46.012 --> 15:47.678
of violent incidents involving..."

15:47.680 --> 15:49.897
I know what it fuckin' says
because I signed that fuckin' thing!

15:49.932 --> 15:50.758
Check!

15:50.783 --> 15:52.783
- "If these conditions are met, any..."
- You gonna continue reading?

15:54.069 --> 15:56.020
There's a whole bunch of
fuckin' big words in there

15:56.022 --> 15:57.488
that you might not even fuckin' understand!

15:57.523 --> 16:00.024
"...Alcohol, Tobacco,
Firearms, Explosives and Cults!

16:00.026 --> 16:02.860
Please contact the Bureau immediately!"

16:02.911 --> 16:05.163
Immediately!

16:05.197 --> 16:07.665
How about I immediately shove
that fuckin' thing up your ass?!

16:07.699 --> 16:08.866
LUCY: Chief Garvey!

16:08.868 --> 16:10.501
Fat fuck.

16:12.671 --> 16:15.122
What's up, gentlemen?

16:15.174 --> 16:18.042
Detective Vitello took it
upon himself to call the feds

16:18.093 --> 16:19.794
- and punt on our homicide.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

16:19.845 --> 16:22.013
I was just doing my job by
following the guidelines...

16:22.047 --> 16:23.214
- Lou?
- Yeah?

16:23.216 --> 16:26.050
Shut the fuck up. Who'd
you talk to at ATFEC?

16:26.101 --> 16:27.885
Agent...

16:27.936 --> 16:29.353
uh, Sean Kilaney.

16:29.388 --> 16:33.057
Great. Please give Agent
Kilaney's contact information

16:33.059 --> 16:36.310
to your boss, so that
he can undo your fuck-up.

16:43.535 --> 16:45.236
Thank you.

16:45.287 --> 16:48.239
You need anything from me?

16:49.458 --> 16:50.908
Curfew.

16:50.910 --> 16:53.077
Nobody out past dark.

16:54.463 --> 16:56.414
Look, the town feels a response,

16:56.416 --> 16:58.583
and if the G.R. violates, I can arrest 'em.

16:58.585 --> 17:00.585
I'll call a council meeting for tomorrow.

17:00.587 --> 17:02.253
Can you be there to make your case?

17:02.304 --> 17:03.754
I just made my case.

17:03.756 --> 17:05.890
It's a formality, Kevin.

17:11.313 --> 17:12.730
I trust you,

17:12.763 --> 17:15.266
but this is a fucking mess.

17:15.268 --> 17:17.734
Lots of eyes on us.

17:17.769 --> 17:20.771
You won't be influenced by your...

17:20.772 --> 17:23.023
family situation?

17:23.075 --> 17:24.608
No.

17:24.660 --> 17:26.359
I won't.

17:36.788 --> 17:38.172
MAN: MasterCard gets us miles.

17:38.206 --> 17:39.624
WOMAN: We haven't flown in two years.

17:39.675 --> 17:40.791
Miles are meaningless.

17:40.842 --> 17:42.426
They're obviously not meaningless.

17:42.461 --> 17:43.961
- Yes, they are.
- Why do you keep saying that?

17:43.963 --> 17:45.463
OK, then. Just wait. Oh...

17:45.465 --> 17:46.931
Can you pull my wallet from the front?

17:46.965 --> 17:48.299
- I got it, I got it. I did, I did, I did.
- You got it?

17:48.301 --> 17:49.467
I did. Yeah. All right.

17:49.469 --> 17:50.851
Amanda.

17:50.886 --> 17:53.387
Amanda, stop staring.

17:53.438 --> 17:55.523
You, too.

17:56.975 --> 18:00.528
♪

18:01.563 --> 18:03.147
Go.

18:31.802 --> 18:33.951
_

19:11.117 --> 19:15.120
RECORDING: Hey, Sean Kilaney at Alcohol,
Tobacco, Firearms, Explosives and Cults.

19:15.154 --> 19:17.322
Leave a message and I'll hit you back.

19:17.324 --> 19:18.740
[Click, beep]

19:18.791 --> 19:21.793
Agent Kilaney, Chief Kevin
Garvey from Mapleton, New York.

19:21.828 --> 19:24.496
Uh, one of our investigators
just spoke to you

19:24.498 --> 19:26.965
about a possible cult-related incident,

19:26.999 --> 19:30.335
but his assessment was premature, so
we'd like to handle that ourselves.

19:30.337 --> 19:34.139
If you give me a call back,
I'd appreciate it. Thanks.

20:02.101 --> 20:04.369
[Dogs barking]

20:04.420 --> 20:06.037
Hey! Hey!

20:06.089 --> 20:07.923
Heh! Sorry.

20:07.957 --> 20:09.291
They're loud, but they're harmless.

20:09.342 --> 20:10.959
Hey! Hey!

20:11.010 --> 20:13.095
Don't worry about it.

20:14.464 --> 20:16.932
Stakin' out the Moonies, huh?

20:16.966 --> 20:19.151
They made an offer on my house.

20:19.185 --> 20:21.603
Guess they're running out of room.

20:21.637 --> 20:23.688
Bought a church, too, I heard.

20:23.723 --> 20:25.140
Yeah.

20:25.191 --> 20:27.109
[Dogs panting]

20:27.143 --> 20:29.561
One of 'em got killed, huh?

20:29.612 --> 20:32.647
Sorry, I'm not allowed to
discuss ongoing investigations.

20:32.698 --> 20:34.616
[Man scoffs]

20:34.650 --> 20:36.902
Don't investigate too hard.

20:36.953 --> 20:39.070
[Dogs barking]

20:42.625 --> 20:44.576
[Line ringing]

20:44.578 --> 20:46.244
- [Click]
- DENNIS: Hello?

20:46.246 --> 20:48.246
Dennis, it's me. Yeah, Chief?

20:48.297 --> 20:50.248
Look, I want you to go and pick up

20:50.250 --> 20:53.168
Reverend Jamison, bring him in.

21:01.227 --> 21:03.345
[Dishes clattering]

21:07.984 --> 21:10.185
Morning, Mr. Garvey.

21:10.236 --> 21:11.486
Why isn't the alarm on?

21:11.521 --> 21:13.104
You didn't text me.

21:13.156 --> 21:16.107
I didn't want it to go off in the
middle of the night when you got home.

21:16.159 --> 21:19.277
Well, that defeats the purpose.

21:23.282 --> 21:25.167
Please, just set it.

21:25.201 --> 21:26.785
KEVIN: OK?

21:29.455 --> 21:32.123
Mr. Garvey, we heard that
the woman who got killed

21:32.175 --> 21:34.176
got dragged behind a
truck and, like, crucified.

21:34.210 --> 21:36.678
- Is that true?
- He's not gonna tell you.

21:36.712 --> 21:38.346
No, Aimee, it's not true.

21:38.381 --> 21:39.931
See?

21:41.300 --> 21:43.218
What a relief.

21:49.725 --> 21:52.194
[Footfalls ascending stairs]

21:52.228 --> 21:54.312
Is she OK?

21:55.781 --> 21:57.449
She's Jill.

21:57.483 --> 22:00.202
- [Door closes upstairs]
- What does that mean?

22:00.236 --> 22:03.705
She doesn't really do OK.

22:03.739 --> 22:06.374
Can't win.

22:06.409 --> 22:08.326
Now you're gettin' it.

22:32.598 --> 22:34.587
_

22:42.912 --> 22:46.531
♪

23:03.215 --> 23:05.216
You look nice.

23:05.218 --> 23:07.218
Have a seat.

23:07.270 --> 23:09.220
Hungry?

23:09.222 --> 23:11.640
They got all-day breakfast here.

23:16.937 --> 23:19.572
What can I get for you, hon?

23:22.743 --> 23:24.577
Can we have a minute, please?

23:24.579 --> 23:26.212
Sure.

23:27.581 --> 23:30.666
How long has it been since
you've spoken, Laurie?

23:31.919 --> 23:33.920
About 7 months?

23:33.971 --> 23:36.088
Eight. Right.

23:37.507 --> 23:39.425
Well, Laurie,

23:39.427 --> 23:41.928
you are overdue for a day off.

23:43.180 --> 23:44.981
No, no,

23:45.015 --> 23:47.066
You can talk.

23:47.100 --> 23:50.569
Just for today. Say anything you want to.

23:50.604 --> 23:53.773
Hey, I'm doing it, too, right?

23:53.824 --> 23:55.942
Are you ready?

24:02.366 --> 24:04.951
PATTI: She's gonna have French toast,

24:05.002 --> 24:08.204
scrambled eggs, order of bacon,
large orange juice. Coffee?

24:08.255 --> 24:10.172
She's gonna have coffee.

24:10.207 --> 24:12.458
WAITRESS: Coffee. You got it.

24:14.378 --> 24:16.963
This is fuckin' good.

24:30.360 --> 24:34.864
RECORDING: Hey, Sean Kilaney at Alcohol,
Tobacco, Firearms, Explosives and Cults.

24:34.898 --> 24:36.916
Leave a message and I'll hit you back.

24:36.950 --> 24:38.150
[Click, beep]

24:38.152 --> 24:39.618
Agent Kilaney, uh,

24:39.653 --> 24:41.620
Kevin Garvey again from Mapleton.

24:41.655 --> 24:43.622
I left you a message last night,

24:43.657 --> 24:45.624
but I haven't heard back.

24:45.659 --> 24:48.127
Please call me. It's important.

24:48.161 --> 24:50.396
Hey, Officer Mustard Stain.

24:50.430 --> 24:51.831
Dropping off or what?

24:51.882 --> 24:54.216
I'm actually picking up. You
got some of my shirts here.

24:54.251 --> 24:55.718
Yeah, sure. You have a ticket?

24:55.752 --> 24:58.254
Just check the computer.
It's under Garvey.

24:58.305 --> 25:00.256
No ticket, no?

25:00.307 --> 25:02.058
No, no ticket.

25:02.092 --> 25:04.443
[Mutters in foreign language]

25:06.313 --> 25:08.264
OK, you pick up last Tuesday.

25:08.315 --> 25:09.849
No, I know, I know I picked up,

25:09.851 --> 25:11.767
but I'm missing my white shirts.

25:11.818 --> 25:13.319
Can you just check again?

25:13.353 --> 25:15.688
[Speaking foreign language]

25:15.739 --> 25:19.859
[Man laughs, speaks foreign language]

25:21.778 --> 25:23.879
Sorry. No shirts, huh?

25:23.914 --> 25:26.165
You didn't even look.

25:26.199 --> 25:27.616
I looked on computer.
Unless you have ticket...

25:27.667 --> 25:28.751
I don't have a ticket.

25:28.785 --> 25:31.420
If they turn up, we'll call you. OK?

25:31.455 --> 25:33.706
Mr. Extra Starch!

25:33.757 --> 25:35.207
Dropping off or what?

25:35.258 --> 25:36.375
Yeah.

25:36.426 --> 25:38.344
Don't give up.

25:38.378 --> 25:41.363
They want you to surrender so they can
sell your shirts on the black market.

25:41.398 --> 25:43.966
- Stay strong.
- Oh. I hope you have a ticket.

25:44.017 --> 25:46.385
I always have a ticket.

25:46.436 --> 25:47.520
Oh.

25:47.554 --> 25:48.971
Well, you know what they say.

25:49.022 --> 25:50.940
They'll turn up once you
stop looking for them.

25:50.974 --> 25:53.059
You think so?

25:53.061 --> 25:54.560
No, probably not.

25:54.562 --> 25:57.229
[Both chuckle]

25:59.066 --> 26:01.283
All right, uh, see you later, Nora.

26:01.318 --> 26:02.785
Bye.

26:02.819 --> 26:05.237
- MAN: Mr. Four Eyes!
- Yes.

26:05.288 --> 26:07.239
Where are we?

26:07.241 --> 26:09.241
Statements from the Moonies.

26:09.243 --> 26:11.210
I didn't check the spelling.

26:11.244 --> 26:14.747
Oh, Dennis has your priest in the war room.

26:14.749 --> 26:17.917
Gonna give him your confession?

26:23.357 --> 26:24.891
Hey, Matt.

26:28.061 --> 26:30.784
Thanks for coming in.

26:32.620 --> 26:34.621
[Sighs]

26:34.623 --> 26:37.758
So...

26:37.792 --> 26:40.961
where were you two nights ago?

26:40.963 --> 26:42.846
Why?

26:42.881 --> 26:44.681
Well,

26:44.716 --> 26:46.717
according to the hospital,
you had a rock thrown

26:46.768 --> 26:48.552
at you a couple months ago,

26:48.603 --> 26:50.471
one aimed at the G.R.

26:50.522 --> 26:53.056
Then they repaid your
generosity by buying up

26:53.108 --> 26:57.111
your church out from under
you, and they painted it white.

26:57.145 --> 26:59.613
You, uh, think I had something to do

26:59.647 --> 27:01.398
with what happened to that woman?

27:01.449 --> 27:02.816
No.

27:02.867 --> 27:04.818
Just want to know where you
were a couple nights ago.

27:04.869 --> 27:07.321
I was at my house with my study group.

27:07.372 --> 27:09.323
A few of them spent the night.

27:09.325 --> 27:11.992
I appreciate the extra help with Mary.

27:11.994 --> 27:14.161
Can you give me their names?

27:14.212 --> 27:15.829
Of course.

27:23.221 --> 27:25.172
The, uh, woman.

27:25.174 --> 27:27.007
Did she have any family?

27:27.058 --> 27:28.509
Why?

27:28.511 --> 27:30.511
Well, back when I had the church,

27:30.513 --> 27:32.012
I used to see her sometimes.

27:32.014 --> 27:35.015
She'd just stand outside the way they do.

27:35.017 --> 27:38.018
She never talked to me, of course, but...

27:38.069 --> 27:39.520
I don't know.

27:39.522 --> 27:42.523
She became a familiar face.

27:42.525 --> 27:44.691
Do you think I could see her?

27:44.693 --> 27:46.860
What, her body?

27:48.246 --> 27:50.197
Yes.

27:50.199 --> 27:52.749
You do realize you're a suspect, Matt?

27:52.784 --> 27:54.751
Well, obviously, but once I'm not,

27:54.786 --> 27:56.837
I'd like to pray for her.

27:59.958 --> 28:01.875
Please?

28:01.926 --> 28:04.294
It'll just be 5 minutes.

28:05.713 --> 28:08.515
No. You can't see her.

28:09.884 --> 28:11.885
[Knock on door]

28:11.887 --> 28:13.687
Hey, Chief, it's 3:00.

28:13.721 --> 28:15.055
They're all in Town Hall, waiting for you.

28:15.106 --> 28:16.857
What? Who?

28:16.891 --> 28:18.809
The mayor, the curfew thing.

28:18.860 --> 28:20.394
Oh, shit!

28:25.316 --> 28:28.569
LUCY: Please, everyone calm down.

28:28.571 --> 28:30.787
I really do appreciate your patience.

28:30.822 --> 28:33.123
Just a few more moments, I promise you.

28:33.157 --> 28:34.308
What the fuck?

28:34.342 --> 28:35.792
They just showed up. I didn't know.

28:35.827 --> 28:37.911
WOMAN: What, I'm not allowed
to leave my own house?

28:37.962 --> 28:39.463
How long is this gonna last?

28:39.497 --> 28:41.465
LUCY: Please, hold your questions.

28:41.499 --> 28:43.217
Chief Garvey suggested the curfew,

28:43.251 --> 28:45.419
and he's here to explain
exactly how it will go.

28:45.421 --> 28:46.386
Chief?

28:46.421 --> 28:48.422
[Whispers] Really?

28:48.424 --> 28:50.424
Um... ahem...

28:50.426 --> 28:54.428
well, M-Ms. Mayor, uh...

28:54.430 --> 28:56.897
I'm sure you're all aware

28:56.931 --> 28:58.982
that a violent hate crime occurred

28:59.017 --> 29:01.268
a couple nights ago

29:01.319 --> 29:03.704
to a member of the Guilty Remnant.

29:03.738 --> 29:06.240
While we conduct our
investigation, I thought

29:06.274 --> 29:08.909
it would be in the best
interests of the town

29:08.943 --> 29:12.529
if people remained in
their homes after 8 p.m.

29:12.580 --> 29:13.447
I work nights!

29:13.498 --> 29:15.165
I'm sure we can make exceptions

29:15.199 --> 29:16.867
if you have to get to a job.

29:16.918 --> 29:19.503
WOMAN: So we have to change
our lives because of them?

29:19.537 --> 29:20.837
CROWD: Yeah!

29:20.872 --> 29:22.306
They broke into my house on Christmas.

29:22.373 --> 29:24.675
People, please, look, we're just
trying to keep everybody safe.

29:24.709 --> 29:26.710
DEAN: Well, you're not
trying to keep us safe.

29:26.761 --> 29:28.128
That's right.

29:28.179 --> 29:30.130
[Scattered shouting dies down]

29:30.181 --> 29:31.381
Excuse me?

29:31.432 --> 29:34.351
It just doesn't seem fair,

29:34.385 --> 29:37.471
us being locked up inside our houses.

29:37.522 --> 29:38.889
We didn't do anything wrong.

29:38.940 --> 29:40.607
CROWD: Yeah.

29:40.642 --> 29:43.644
I mean, with all due respect, Chief,

29:43.646 --> 29:47.481
how do we even know these people
didn't do this to themselves?

29:47.483 --> 29:50.534
Because you were with them
when they found the body.

29:50.568 --> 29:52.152
Well, I was with some of them.

29:52.154 --> 29:54.988
What are you... you don't even live here.

29:55.039 --> 29:56.990
Well, sure I do.

29:56.992 --> 30:00.127
And when I moved here, hell,
it seemed like a nice place.

30:00.161 --> 30:02.663
- Oh, are you fuckin' serious?!
- LUCY: OK.

30:02.714 --> 30:05.165
I think everyone's had their say.

30:05.216 --> 30:07.634
This is not a public vote.

30:07.669 --> 30:09.636
It's for the council alone.

30:09.671 --> 30:12.673
- [Crowd murmuring]
- And, for the record,

30:12.724 --> 30:15.676
I fully support Chief Garvey.

30:15.678 --> 30:18.178
All in favor of imposing

30:18.180 --> 30:20.480
an emergency town-wide curfew to start

30:20.515 --> 30:23.817
at 8 p.m., effective this evening?

30:28.856 --> 30:30.273
All opposed?

30:30.325 --> 30:31.858
Yeah.

30:38.416 --> 30:40.867
[Applause]

30:40.918 --> 30:44.554
♪

30:49.878 --> 30:51.879
[Knock on door]

30:58.103 --> 31:00.187
Where's Patti?

31:01.890 --> 31:05.109
Get all your people
together here in 5 minutes

31:05.143 --> 31:07.561
from all your fuckin' houses.

31:08.980 --> 31:10.314
I'll wait.

31:17.038 --> 31:21.992
It's just been made clear to me that
it's officially open season on you people.

31:22.043 --> 31:25.713
Now, the ideal thing would be for
you all to stay off the streets,

31:25.747 --> 31:28.883
but we all know that's
not gonna happen, is it?

31:31.636 --> 31:33.087
Whistles.

31:33.089 --> 31:37.057
Keep these on you at all times. Use them.

31:37.092 --> 31:40.094
I got my people on extra patrols,
and they're ready to respond.

31:40.145 --> 31:42.646
This doesn't have to happen again,

31:42.681 --> 31:44.598
but that's on you.

31:44.649 --> 31:46.734
No one understands whatever
it is you believe in.

31:46.768 --> 31:50.738
They don't give a shit...
long as you leave them alone.

31:50.772 --> 31:53.774
But if you keep following people
around, buying up their homes,

31:53.776 --> 31:56.243
painting everything white,

31:56.278 --> 31:59.914
breaking into their
houses, they will retaliate.

32:02.083 --> 32:04.168
Any questions?

32:09.090 --> 32:11.458
I'll take them in writing.

32:13.011 --> 32:16.213
♪

32:16.264 --> 32:18.382
Thank you for your time.

32:29.728 --> 32:32.313
It's Meg, right?

32:33.732 --> 32:35.866
Do you still talk?

32:35.900 --> 32:38.118
Yes.

32:39.321 --> 32:40.988
Where's Laurie?

32:41.039 --> 32:43.123
I don't know.

32:44.492 --> 32:46.994
Is she OK?

32:46.996 --> 32:49.330
I don't know.

32:49.381 --> 32:52.166
I'm the only person that
gives a shit about you people,

32:52.217 --> 32:54.835
and you won't even tell
me where my wife is?

32:56.221 --> 32:59.290
She's not your wife anymore.

33:14.272 --> 33:16.190
WAITRESS: OK. All done, girls?

33:16.241 --> 33:18.192
- Oh, we are indeed.
- [Chuckles]

33:18.243 --> 33:20.694
Just the check. Mm-hmm.

33:20.745 --> 33:23.364
Oh, could I have a doggie bag, please?

33:23.415 --> 33:25.366
For what?

33:25.417 --> 33:28.202
Just get me the bag, sweetheart.

33:28.204 --> 33:29.837
OK.

33:33.425 --> 33:36.377
I brought her here, too.

33:36.428 --> 33:38.846
Just over a year ago.

33:38.880 --> 33:42.049
Gladys sat right there where
you're sittin' right now.

33:43.435 --> 33:46.103
I don't know how, but she somehow got word

33:46.137 --> 33:48.555
that her son had died.

33:48.606 --> 33:51.892
Did she ever tell you she had a son?

33:51.894 --> 33:53.360
No.

33:53.395 --> 33:55.863
It was over in Yemen, I think.

33:55.897 --> 33:59.400
His helicopter just crashed or some such,

33:59.402 --> 34:01.452
and as you can imagine,

34:01.486 --> 34:03.904
she did not take it very well.

34:03.955 --> 34:07.658
She questioned her commitment,
she became distracted,

34:07.709 --> 34:11.495
and she began to feel again.

34:12.964 --> 34:16.382
And there was a lot of mopin'
and cryin' around the house,

34:16.418 --> 34:18.886
and then it started to happen

34:18.920 --> 34:21.054
out in the open.

34:26.928 --> 34:29.847
So I brought her here, I fed her,

34:29.898 --> 34:33.400
and I invited her to speak
her troubles out loud.

34:33.435 --> 34:37.438
I gave her every opportunity to talk.

34:37.489 --> 34:40.440
She never spoke one word,

34:40.492 --> 34:42.609
never broke,

34:42.659 --> 34:45.279
just like you.

34:47.665 --> 34:50.117
So I'm going to tell you

34:50.168 --> 34:52.703
what I told her.

34:57.459 --> 35:00.427
I understand the pull.

35:00.462 --> 35:03.764
♪

35:03.798 --> 35:07.301
I understand. It's your family.

35:07.303 --> 35:09.803
It's your past.

35:09.805 --> 35:12.272
I understand

35:12.307 --> 35:15.809
that going back to them feels comfortable

35:15.811 --> 35:18.779
and easy

35:18.813 --> 35:22.616
because the alternative, what we do,

35:22.650 --> 35:25.736
is very, very hard.

35:29.657 --> 35:33.293
But there can't be any doubt, Laurie...

35:35.713 --> 35:37.664
because doubt

35:37.666 --> 35:40.167
is fire!

35:40.169 --> 35:43.670
And fire is gonna burn you up

35:43.672 --> 35:46.340
until you are but ash!

35:51.179 --> 35:53.647
[Footsteps approach]

35:53.681 --> 35:56.016
OK. Ladies, come see us again.

35:57.986 --> 35:59.653
[Kiss]

35:59.687 --> 36:01.438
Yeah.

36:05.193 --> 36:06.693
[Sighs]

36:06.695 --> 36:08.529
[Chuckles]

36:11.166 --> 36:15.836
You remember what you told me
to do in the last session...

36:17.288 --> 36:19.756
just before everything changed?

36:22.677 --> 36:24.261
[Whimpering]

36:31.686 --> 36:33.770
[Laughs]

36:33.777 --> 36:35.279
_

36:36.691 --> 36:38.725
Can I be excused,

36:38.727 --> 36:40.861
please?

36:42.647 --> 36:44.231
Yeah.

36:59.130 --> 37:01.665
[Matt speaking inside]

37:08.640 --> 37:10.757
[Applause inside]

37:21.769 --> 37:25.072
OK, Reverend. You want
to pray over her? Fine.

37:25.106 --> 37:27.858
What made you change your mind?

37:27.909 --> 37:30.911
The closest thing she's gonna
get to a funeral... oh, shit.

37:36.284 --> 37:38.752
Jesus said to his disciples,

37:38.786 --> 37:42.756
"Compare me to something
and tell me what I am like."

37:42.790 --> 37:45.876
And Thomas said to him, "Teacher,

37:45.927 --> 37:49.763
my mouth is utterly unable
to say what you are like."

37:49.797 --> 37:52.799
And Jesus said, "I am not your teacher

37:52.850 --> 37:55.435
"because you have become intoxicated

37:55.470 --> 37:58.939
from the bubbling spring I have tended."

37:58.973 --> 38:01.108
And he took Thomas and withdrew

38:01.142 --> 38:04.027
and spoke 3 sayings to him.

38:04.062 --> 38:06.363
When Thomas came back,
his friends asked him,

38:06.397 --> 38:08.649
"What did Jesus say to you?"

38:08.651 --> 38:11.485
And Thomas responded,

38:11.487 --> 38:14.488
"If I tell you what he spoke to me,

38:14.490 --> 38:16.957
"you will pick up rocks and stone me,

38:16.991 --> 38:21.295
and fire will come from
the rocks and devour you."

38:26.634 --> 38:28.552
[Chuckles]

38:28.586 --> 38:31.004
You want to tell me what that means?

38:31.055 --> 38:33.006
[Chuckles]

38:33.008 --> 38:35.509
It means it's easier to stay silent

38:35.511 --> 38:37.678
than it is to speak truth.

38:39.597 --> 38:42.516
Killing these people is pointless.

38:42.567 --> 38:45.686
They don't care because
they're already dead.

38:45.737 --> 38:49.189
♪

38:49.240 --> 38:53.660
You know, what I want is
to bring them back to life.

39:20.422 --> 39:22.757
Oh. Sorry about that.

39:22.808 --> 39:25.142
[Closes drawer]

39:25.177 --> 39:27.261
Must be that one.

39:31.400 --> 39:33.401
Uh, Billy?

39:33.435 --> 39:36.771
What happened to the D.B. in 4? Female?

39:36.773 --> 39:38.406
BILLY: Oh, we shipped her out.

39:38.440 --> 39:40.191
You fuckin' shipped her? Where?

39:40.242 --> 39:43.744
Sorry. We got an email ordering
us to send her out to Virginia.

39:43.779 --> 39:47.748
Uh, it was from... Agent Kilaney.

39:47.783 --> 39:50.201
It says you guys called him.

39:50.252 --> 39:54.422
RECORDING: Hey, Sean Kilaney at Alcohol,
Tobacco, Firearms, Explosives and Cults.

39:54.456 --> 39:56.390
Leave a message and I'll hit you back.

39:56.425 --> 39:58.876
- [Beep]
- Listen, asshole, you don't call me back

39:58.927 --> 40:02.380
and then you email my morgue
and you pull my fuckin' body?!

40:02.431 --> 40:05.049
If you don't call me back within
the hour, I will be in my car

40:05.100 --> 40:08.803
driving to D.C., where I will
personally hit you fuckin' back!

40:08.805 --> 40:10.771
Understood?!

40:10.806 --> 40:13.274
It's Kevin Garvey from Mapleton!

40:13.308 --> 40:15.943
- [Hangs up, stomps]
- Fuck!

40:17.813 --> 40:20.314
I say fuck, too.

40:20.316 --> 40:22.283
[Sighs]

40:22.317 --> 40:25.987
♪

40:30.659 --> 40:32.793
[Closes van door]

40:56.768 --> 41:00.271
[Door opens, key-in-ignition
warning chimes]

41:00.322 --> 41:02.356
[Door closes]

41:07.746 --> 41:10.862
[Music stops, engine turns over]

41:14.701 --> 41:17.336
[Security system beeping]

41:18.705 --> 41:21.673
WOMAN'S VOICE: Disarm system now.

41:21.708 --> 41:23.675
[Beeping continues]

41:23.710 --> 41:25.711
- Disarm system now.
- Oh, shit.

41:25.713 --> 41:28.180
[Cell phone vibrating]

41:28.214 --> 41:30.849
- Disarm system now.
- Shit.

41:32.218 --> 41:35.187
Disarm system now.

41:35.221 --> 41:37.856
- [Burglar alarm blaring]
- Fuck!

41:40.226 --> 41:42.060
Uhh! Fuck.

41:42.111 --> 41:43.562
Fuck.

41:43.613 --> 41:45.864
Oh, shit.

41:45.898 --> 41:48.066
- [Alarm continues blaring]
- Oh, shit.

41:48.068 --> 41:49.568
Fuck!

41:49.570 --> 41:51.069
[Alarm stops]

41:51.071 --> 41:53.038
System deactivated.

41:53.072 --> 41:55.490
[Panting] Hello?

41:55.541 --> 41:58.543
Hey, Chief Harvey. Sean
Kilaney from ATFEC. How are ya?

41:58.578 --> 42:01.546
Sorry I didn't get back to you
sooner. I was down in Florida.

42:01.581 --> 42:03.582
Fuckin' mess. You see it on the news?

42:03.616 --> 42:05.083
No.

42:05.085 --> 42:07.085
Count yourself lucky.

42:07.087 --> 42:09.638
- So, uh, you got a cult-related homicide?
- [Opens bottle]

42:09.672 --> 42:12.174
- Didn't you get my messages?
- Well, just one. You leave more?

42:12.225 --> 42:14.726
Now, you want us to
take jurisdiction, right?

42:14.761 --> 42:17.679
Uh... uh, no. Don't worry about it.

42:17.730 --> 42:20.716
Um, listen, you never
should have gotten that call.

42:20.750 --> 42:23.235
One of my detectives
jumped the gun. Vitello.

42:23.269 --> 42:25.237
- Oh.
- He said he spoke to you.

42:25.271 --> 42:28.240
Oh, OK. Let me, uh, pull it up here. Uh...

42:28.274 --> 42:31.777
Got it. Jesus. Right. The stoning.

42:31.828 --> 42:34.162
Fuck. The victim was
what, Tomorrow's Family?

42:34.197 --> 42:35.664
No, Guilty Remnant.

42:35.698 --> 42:37.449
Oh, those nuts.

42:37.500 --> 42:39.618
What's up with the chain-smoking?

42:39.620 --> 42:42.621
Look, you know what? It sounds
like you got your hands full.

42:42.623 --> 42:45.540
They sent the body to you a couple
hours ago, and it's not like...

42:45.591 --> 42:48.543
Shit. They did?

42:48.594 --> 42:50.462
They said you emailed them.

42:50.513 --> 42:53.181
Uh, that's automated. It
gets sent to the local M.E.

42:53.216 --> 42:55.684
as soon as I put a Tier 3 in the system.

42:55.718 --> 42:58.637
Well, then send her back
to me. Send the body back.

42:58.688 --> 43:02.641
Yeah, wish I could. She's en route
to our forensic processing center.

43:02.692 --> 43:05.143
Then how 'bout I come down
there, I pick her up myself?

43:05.194 --> 43:08.880
Uh, sorry. Once she's in the
system, there's nothing I can do.

43:08.915 --> 43:11.316
Well, what about, uh,

43:11.367 --> 43:13.819
forensics, evidence,
our witness statements?

43:13.870 --> 43:15.821
- You know what?
- You want me to...

43:15.872 --> 43:17.739
You go ahead and hold
on to all of that, OK?

43:17.790 --> 43:20.325
You should be hearing from
one of our field guys soon.

43:20.327 --> 43:22.327
In how long?

43:22.329 --> 43:25.297
Uh, 4 to 6 weeks.

43:25.331 --> 43:26.998
[Sighs] Oh, fuck.

43:27.049 --> 43:28.917
Or, if you want,

43:28.968 --> 43:31.503
we could just eliminate the infestation.

43:31.505 --> 43:32.971
Excuse me?

43:33.005 --> 43:37.426
I can have 3 vans full of armed
agents there by the end of the week.

43:37.477 --> 43:40.929
They pay a visit to whatever
compound these fucks call home,

43:40.980 --> 43:44.015
and they get you the
results you're lookin' for.

43:44.017 --> 43:45.484
Chief...

43:45.518 --> 43:48.153
this shit spreads if you let it.

43:49.522 --> 43:53.024
Don't worry about your victim.
She doesn't give a shit.

43:53.026 --> 43:55.494
Worry about your town.

43:55.528 --> 43:58.530
♪

43:58.532 --> 44:00.499
And, uh... ahem.

44:00.533 --> 44:02.667
The Guilty Remnant. What happens...

44:02.702 --> 44:04.870
what would happen to them?

44:04.872 --> 44:06.872
What happens is

44:06.874 --> 44:09.007
they go away.

44:09.041 --> 44:11.877
They're not your problem anymore.

44:11.879 --> 44:13.845
Just say the word,

44:13.880 --> 44:16.882
and everything can go back to normal.

44:16.884 --> 44:20.018
Well, I appreciate that.

44:22.889 --> 44:24.890
Hello?

44:24.892 --> 44:26.892
You still there?

44:26.894 --> 44:28.393
Chief?

44:28.395 --> 44:31.530
Uh... uh...

44:32.899 --> 44:35.901
Uh, but no thanks.

44:35.903 --> 44:38.403
We can handle it.

44:38.405 --> 44:40.288
OK.

44:40.323 --> 44:42.824
Good luck with that, Chief.

44:42.875 --> 44:44.810
[Hangs up]

44:44.844 --> 44:48.463
♪

44:52.735 --> 44:54.753
♪

44:54.755 --> 44:56.888
[Item falls to floor]

45:07.600 --> 45:11.520
Sorry, I can't sell alcohol to
people who are already enibritted.

45:11.571 --> 45:12.571
Who are what?

45:12.605 --> 45:13.939
Enibritted.

45:13.941 --> 45:15.407
Oh. Inebriated?

45:15.441 --> 45:17.275
- Yeah.
- Oh, I'm not, so

45:17.277 --> 45:19.277
promise you won't get in any trouble.

45:19.279 --> 45:21.112
All right. [Sighs]

45:21.163 --> 45:24.249
- [Cash register beeps]
- So, you guys, uh,

45:24.283 --> 45:26.501
catch who killed that lady yet?

45:26.536 --> 45:28.003
No.

45:28.037 --> 45:30.121
We have not.

45:44.804 --> 45:47.305
[Distant man laughing]

45:47.307 --> 45:49.941
[Speaking foreign language]

45:57.817 --> 45:59.484
Hey.

45:59.486 --> 46:01.570
- [Laughing]
- Hey!

46:03.906 --> 46:05.323
Open the door.

46:05.374 --> 46:06.825
- We're closed.
- No, no, no.

46:06.876 --> 46:08.493
It's me, Officer Mustard Stain.

46:08.544 --> 46:10.328
Open the door.

46:11.714 --> 46:12.881
- Open the door.
- We're closed!

46:12.915 --> 46:14.332
Sorry, sir. We're closed.

46:14.383 --> 46:15.867
- OK?
- Oh, I'm a sir now?

46:15.902 --> 46:18.336
Now I'm a sir. Open the door!

46:18.338 --> 46:21.894
Hang up the phone and
open this door right now!

46:21.945 --> 46:23.946
Please, if you come back tomorrow...

46:23.980 --> 46:26.065
Open the door.

46:27.484 --> 46:29.068
Sir! You cannot...

46:29.070 --> 46:30.069
Oh, I cannot?!

46:30.071 --> 46:31.203
I cannot?

46:31.238 --> 46:33.372
Open the motherfuckin' door right now!

46:33.406 --> 46:35.407
OK, OK. O-OK.

46:42.415 --> 46:45.918
Please, please. We're... what do you want?

46:45.969 --> 46:47.419
[Panting]

46:47.421 --> 46:51.006
I want you to look for my shirts,

46:51.057 --> 46:53.726
and I would appreciate it if
you fuckin' tried this time.

46:53.760 --> 46:55.761
Yes, yes. Of course. Please.

46:55.763 --> 46:57.730
Let me... uh,

46:57.764 --> 46:59.732
how many... how many shirts?

46:59.766 --> 47:01.317
- Eight.
- Eight.

47:02.736 --> 47:04.270
And... and, uh,

47:04.272 --> 47:06.155
- what color?
- All white!

47:06.189 --> 47:07.656
Uh, here we are.

47:07.691 --> 47:09.275
All white shirts, huh?

47:09.326 --> 47:10.860
- That's right.
- Here we are.

47:12.579 --> 47:15.030
I've got them. They're
here. Yeah. One second.

47:16.449 --> 47:17.500
Yes.

47:17.534 --> 47:19.502
See? White shirts.

47:19.536 --> 47:21.504
Here you go.

47:21.538 --> 47:23.506
More white shirts.

47:23.540 --> 47:24.957
That's...

47:25.008 --> 47:26.792
- Here. White.
- Yeah.

47:28.211 --> 47:30.296
White shirts.

47:32.632 --> 47:34.633
- Eight shirts.
- Thank you.

47:34.635 --> 47:36.635
Uh, no, no. It's OK.

47:36.686 --> 47:38.721
No charge, sir.

47:38.772 --> 47:40.306
Our mistake, OK?

47:46.229 --> 47:47.813
Thanks.

47:53.904 --> 47:55.321
[Door opens]

48:14.474 --> 48:16.058
[Sighs]

48:17.583 --> 48:19.357
_

48:24.935 --> 48:28.600
[Microphone feedback]

48:28.635 --> 48:31.687
MATT, OUTSIDE: One, two.
Testing. Testing, testing.

48:31.721 --> 48:34.690
One, two. Good evening.

48:34.724 --> 48:36.642
Hello.

48:36.693 --> 48:39.311
My name is Matt Jamison.

48:40.647 --> 48:43.232
I didn't know your friend very well.

48:43.283 --> 48:46.318
I don't even know if you
considered her a friend,

48:46.320 --> 48:49.988
but she lived here, with all of you.

48:51.157 --> 48:54.126
I tried to give her a blanket once

48:54.160 --> 48:57.963
on a cold winter day,
but she wouldn't take it.

48:57.997 --> 49:00.883
She was committed to her path.

49:00.917 --> 49:04.419
I don't understand your faith,

49:04.471 --> 49:06.922
but I understand commitment

49:06.973 --> 49:09.341
and I respect it.

49:09.392 --> 49:13.428
But we are, all of us, no
matter what we've suffered,

49:13.463 --> 49:14.897
still alive.

49:14.931 --> 49:18.517
We still feel pain and sorrow.

49:18.568 --> 49:21.436
We still feel loss.

49:21.488 --> 49:24.857
We still feel love.

49:24.908 --> 49:28.360
♪

49:28.411 --> 49:32.364
MATT: This woman was one
of you, and now she's gone.

49:32.415 --> 49:35.367
I know you cannot speak her name.

49:35.369 --> 49:38.921
I know you cannot say good-bye.

49:38.955 --> 49:41.423
But I ask you at least

49:41.457 --> 49:43.542
to let me.

49:44.928 --> 49:47.796
If any of you wants to, I invite you now

49:47.847 --> 49:49.965
to come out and join us.

49:54.554 --> 49:58.390
"I lift up my eyes to the hills.

49:58.441 --> 50:01.560
Where does my health come from?"

50:07.033 --> 50:09.902
"It comes from the Lord,

50:09.953 --> 50:12.905
"the Maker of Heaven and Earth.

50:12.956 --> 50:15.908
"He will not let your foot slip.

50:15.959 --> 50:19.461
"He who watches over you will not slumber.

50:19.495 --> 50:21.630
Indeed, He..."

50:21.664 --> 50:23.749
[Blowing whistle]

50:29.672 --> 50:31.723
[Whistling continues]

50:46.739 --> 50:48.156
[Beeping]

50:48.191 --> 50:50.826
WOMAN'S VOICE: Disarm system now.

50:53.246 --> 50:57.841
Disarm system now.

50:57.892 --> 50:59.476
[Beeping stops]

50:59.510 --> 51:01.428
System deactivated.

51:09.353 --> 51:10.987
[Sighs]

51:14.158 --> 51:15.742
JILL: Hey.

51:17.161 --> 51:18.695
I heard the alarm.

51:18.697 --> 51:20.697
I just wanted to make sure it was you.

51:20.748 --> 51:22.749
Oh, thanks for setting it.

51:22.783 --> 51:24.251
Yeah.

51:24.285 --> 51:26.253
Find your shirts?

51:26.287 --> 51:27.904
Yeah.

51:32.760 --> 51:35.879
Your mother and I are getting a divorce.

51:40.635 --> 51:42.219
OK.

51:49.610 --> 51:52.229
[Voice shaking] I'm sorry.

51:54.615 --> 51:56.566
It's not your fault.

51:56.617 --> 51:58.568
Uh...

51:58.619 --> 52:00.737
[Sniffles]

52:02.073 --> 52:04.407
I love you, honey.

52:05.793 --> 52:08.245
I love you, too.

52:08.247 --> 52:11.915
♪

52:22.393 --> 52:24.477
[Sobbing]

